    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="531"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">President of France</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-04-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On the occasion of the formal reception at Annapolis of the body of John Paul
                    Jones I wish to thank you, and through you the great French nation, for its
                    distinguished courtesy in connection with this event, a courtesy of a kind which
                    serves to keep even more vividly before us the invaluable aid rendered by France
                    to this country at what was well nigh the most critical period of its history.
                    France holds a peculiar place in the heart of the American people, and on behalf
                    of that people I wish all success, prosperity, and happiness to the mighty
                    Republic over which you preside.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore Roosevelt.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
